ock_reason":null,"draft":false,"pull_request":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy-project/pulls/390","html_url":"https://github.com/astropy/astropy-project/pull/390","diff_url":"https://github.com/astropy/astropy-project/pull/390.diff","patch_url":"https://github.com/astropy/astropy-project/pull/390.patch","merged_at":null},"body":"The file contains all the relevant info :) ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy-project/issues/390/reactions","total_count":2,"+1":2,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"timeline_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy-project/issues/390/timeline","performed_via_github_app":null,"state_reason":null},"comment":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy-project/issues/comments/2038409463","html_url":"https://github.com/astropy/astropy-project/pull/390#issuecomment-2038409463","issue_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy-project/issues/390","id":2038409463,"node_id":"IC_kwDOBjKRfc55f6j3","user":{"login":"manodeep","id":3004941,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMwMDQ5NDE=","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/3004941?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep","html_url":"https://github.com/manodeep","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/manodeep/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"created_at":"2024-04-04T22:57:13Z","updated_at":"2024-04-04T22:57:13Z","author_association":"NONE","body":"While working on [multi-threaded race condition in wcslib](https://github.com/astropy/astropy/issues/16245), I noticed several potential improvements to the `wcslib` code. The original intent of my PR was not meant for reviewing code within the `cextern` directory - however, may be this is an area that also needs attention. Specifically, I have noticed the following potential improvements in `wcslib`:

- use of confusing assignment and status checking
- use of `0x0` as a special value for null-pointers instead of using the standard `NULL` (which is `(void *) 0` in most (all?) systems. )
- use of `[0, 1]` as return codes instead of the more portable `EXIT_SUCCESS` and `EXIT_FAILURE` (from `<stdlib.h>`)
- mixed use of string handling functions for safer (up to a max numchars)/unsafe with `strncpy/strcpy`. All should be replaced with safer `strlcpy` (which will truncate the source string if necessary but guarantee a terminating `\0` in the destination string). 
- use of a static variable for `static int WCSSET = 137` in multiple C files which would be better off as a macro within `wcs.h` 

These changes above will improve code readability and make the C code more compliant with conventions, but the current C code in `wcslib` (that I have reviewed so far) should generate correct output under most/all (non-hostile) circumstances.

**Additional context for the assignment + status checking**

There are a lot of potentially confusing statements where an [assignment is done and status checked in the same line](https://github.com/astropy/astropy/blob/main/cextern/wcslib/C/wcs.c#L2914) throughout the wcslib C codebase under cextern. These statements would be better off being split into two and replacing `0x0` with `NULL`, e.g.,

```c
if ((wcs->types = calloc(naxis, sizeof(int))) == 0x0) {

//ideally should be broken into two lines as
wcs->types = calloc(naxis, sizeof(int));
if (wcs->types == NULL) {
```

However, making such changes within astropy might cause the cextern package to diverge from upstream and potentially cause maintenance issues in the future. If such changes might be useful for the project, **and** there are funds for tackling them into `wcslib`, then I am happy to take it on (either as part of this FR or a future one). Assuming the existing tests are exhaustive, I would estimate the changes would take ~40 hours to incorporate. ","reactions":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy-project/issues/comments/2038409463/reactions","total_count":0,"+1":0,"-1":0,"laugh":0,"hooray":0,"confused":0,"heart":0,"rocket":0,"eyes":0},"performed_via_github_app":null}}

{"action":"created","issue":{"url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy/issues/16245","repository_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy","labels_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy/issues/16245/labels{/name}","comments_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy/issues/16245/comments","events_url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy/issues/16245/events","html_url":"https://github.com/astropy/astropy/issues/16245","id":2210314292,"node_id":"I_kwDOAB_CCc6Dvrg0","number":16245,"title":"Multi-threading issue in WCSLIB even if input data is copied","user":{"login":"astrofrog","id":314716,"node_id":"MDQ6VXNlcjMxNDcxNg==","avatar_url":"https://avatars.githubusercontent.com/u/314716?v=4","gravatar_id":"","url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog","html_url":"https://github.com/astrofrog","followers_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/followers","following_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/following{/other_user}","gists_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/gists{/gist_id}","starred_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/starred{/owner}{/repo}","subscriptions_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/subscriptions","organizations_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/orgs","repos_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/repos","events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/events{/privacy}","received_events_url":"https://api.github.com/users/astrofrog/received_events","type":"User","site_admin":false},"labels":[{"id":188323,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxODgzMjM=","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy/labels/wcs","name":"wcs","color":"c7def8","default":false,"description":null},{"id":16191481,"node_id":"MDU6TGFiZWwxNjE5MTQ4MQ==","url":"https://api.github.com/repos/astropy/astropy/labels/Bug","name":"Bug","color":"d93f0b","default":false,"description":null}],"state":"open","locked":false,"assignee":null,"assignees":[],"milestone":null,"comments":14,"created_at":"2024-03-27T09:41:08Z","updated_at":"2024-04-05T05:12:41Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"MEMBER","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"In https://github.com/astropy/astropy/issues/16244 I mentioned a multi-threading issue that is due to the input array being passed through to the WCS C extension and being subsequently modified in-place. There is however another issue that occurs even if the input data is copied, and is illustrated by the following example:

```python
import numpy as np
from astropy.wcs import WCS
from multiprocessing.pool import ThreadPool

wcs = WCS(naxis=2)
wcs.wcs.crpix = [-234.75, 8.3393]
wcs.wcs.cdelt = np.array([-0.066667, 0.066667])
wcs.wcs.crval = [0, -90]
wcs.wcs.ctype = ["RA---AIR", "DEC--AIR"]
wcs.wcs.set()

N = 1_000_000

pixel = np.random.randint(-1000, 1000, N * 2).reshape((N, 2)).astype(float)


def round_trip_transform(pixel):
    world = wcs.wcs.p2s(pixel.copy(), 1)['world']
    wcs.wcs.lng  # this access causes issues, without it all works
    pixel = wcs.wcs.s2p(world, 1)['pixcrd']
    return pixel


pool = ThreadPool(8)
results = pool.map(round_trip_transform, (pixel,) * 8)

for pixel2 in results:
    print(
        f"Mismatching elements: {np.sum(~np.isclose(pixel, pixel2))}"
