he compiler is already producing the multiply call anyway.

I had added a for loop on [godbolt](https://godbolt.org/z/7EWzT51Pe) around the `pow` to mimic the actual case within the code and I saw that even with `gcc-13.2` and `-O2` as the compilation flag, the compiler produces `mulsd` - which is the non-vectorised version. If you use `-O2 -ftree-vectorize` or `-O3`, the correct vector call `mulpd` is generated (which should be 2x faster for doubles and 4x faster for floats). 

