eated_at":"2024-03-01T02:01:51Z","updated_at":"2024-03-02T12:00:00Z","closed_at":null,"author_association":"CONTRIBUTOR","active_lock_reason":null,"body":"While looking through the C code, I noticed a [reference](https://github.com/astropy/astropy/blob/47a8dac8f1dab6ce592be6048f70140adead4e1d/astropy/stats/src/compute_bounds.c#L45-L47) to `pow` within a `for` loop. `pow` is a slow operation meant for floating point exponents. Since the exponent here is integral (`==2`), this instance of `pow` should be replaced with a multiply. 

Existing code is:

```c
      for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        std += pow(mean - data_buffer[i], 2);
      }
```

Better performant code would be:

```c
      for (i = 0; i < count; i++) {
        const double dx = mean - data_buffer[i];
        std += dx * dx;
      }
```
